7:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Feature Analysis"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"Both Steve AI and Synthesia share a solid foundation of core features including Text To Video, Auto Captions, Templates, Stock Footage. On the other hand, Synthesia uniquely offers Avatar Talking Head and Screen Recording and Api Access and Batch Processing, giving it an edge for users who prioritize these areas. \n\nLooking at user ratings, Steve AI holds an overall score of 6/10 and an ease of use score of 8/10, while Synthesia scores 8/10 overall and 9/10 for ease of use. These ratings reflect real user experiences and can indicate differences in usability, support quality, and overall satisfaction."}]]}]
8:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Pricing Breakdown"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"When it comes to pricing, Steve AI offers a more budget-friendly entry point at $20/mo, compared to Synthesia's starting price of $22/mo. Both platforms offer free plans, which is great for testing before committing. Steve AI's free tier and Synthesia's free tier each have their own limitations, so it is worth evaluating both to see which free offering better matches your initial needs."}]]}]
