en":"-"}],"Expensive for individuals"]}],["$","li","2",{"style":{"color":"var(--text-secondary)"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"style":{"position":"absolute","left":0,"color":"var(--red)","fontWeight":700},"children":"-"}],"Limited creative freedom"]}],["$","li","3",{"style":{"color":"var(--text-secondary)"},"children":[["$","span",null,{"style":{"position":"absolute","left":0,"color":"var(--red)","fontWeight":700},"children":"-"}],"Corporate-focused"]}]]}]]}]]}]
b:["$","div",null,{"className":"prose","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Who Should Choose Which?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The ideal user for each platform differs considerably. Steve AI is best suited for animated explainer videos, educational content, making it a strong choice if you fall into any of these categories. Synthesia, meanwhile, shines for corporate training videos, multilingual business content, which means it may be the better pick if your needs align with those use cases.\n\nFounded in 2021, Steve AI describes itself as \"Create animated and live-action videos with AI.\" Synthesia, established in 2017, positions itself as \"Create professional AI videos with digital avatars.\" Both platforms have been in the market for a similar duration, giving each ample time to refine their offerings and build a loyal user base."}]]}]
c:["$","div",null,{"className":"verdict-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Our Verdict"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After analyzing all the data, **Synthesia** comes out slightly ahead in this comparison, thanks to higher user ratings (8.0 vs 6.0), more features (9 vs 5), availability of a free plan. However, this does not mean Steve AI is a poor choice — far from it. Steve AI excels in its own right, particularly for animated explainer videos and educational content.\n\nOur recommendation: if you value 160+ realistic ai avatars, go with Synthesia. If good animation styles matters more to you, Steve AI is the way to go. Either way, both are solid platforms that have earned their place in the market."}]]}]
